race.comment: Even race which is reflected in the market. TRANTORO (8) looks an each-way prospect and is worth a bet at the price. He's won two from five at the track and distance. He's drawn barrier three and Toeroek goes on so there is plenty to like. IMMORTAL SHIELD (2) is another that has never run a bad race at Gawler with three placings form three starts here. He can hold a spot from the low draw and give himself every chance of running into the money. COSTLESS (1) is the class horse in the race and appears well placed here. The knock is that he hasn't won for a long time but this might be his chance. DODD (3) and NOT IN DOUBT (5) looks others worth some thought for wider exotics and the quaddie.
